From e5147bd832528bd59b7e048f5d42c6f53ab1da8c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jiucheng Xu <jiucheng.xu@amlogic.com>
Date: Thu, 19 Dec 2024 11:55:45 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ntfs3: fix evict hang issue [1/1]
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

PD#SWPL-197556

Problem:
evicting inode will set I_FREEING for each inode at lru list.
ntfs3 evicting inode will update parent inode， updating inode need
get inode firstly, find_inode() wait until inode.state
is not I_FREEING. this causes kswapd hang.

task:kswapd0/48
[<c0f566c4>] schedule+0x100/0x180
[<c057e604>] find_inode+0x108/0x184
[<c057e8c0>] ilookup5+0xc0/0x13c
[<c057e6fc>] iget5_locked+0x24/0x128
[<bfb775d4>] ntfs_iget5+0x30/0x107c [ntfs3]
[<bfb6cc28>] ni_update_parent+0x2e0/0x3a8 [ntfs3]
[<bfb6c930>] ni_write_inode+0x4b4/0x4cc [ntfs3]
[<bfb7a344>] ntfs_evict_inode+0x38/0x54 [ntfs3]
[<c0580578>] evict+0xb4/0x250
[<c057d9b0>] prune_icache_sb+0x7c/0xa4
[<c0561c1c>] super_cache_scan+0x154/0x188
[<c04ea964>] shrink_slab+0x1d8/0x618
[<c04efbb0>] shrink_node+0xd48/0x10c8
[<c04edc44>] balance_pgdat+0x460/0x77c
[<c04ed5ec>] kswapd+0x2ac/0x4a4
[<c03559e0>] kthread+0x1d8/0x204
[<c0300134>] ret_from_fork+0x14/0x40

Solution:
skip update parent inode when evict inode. parent inode will be updated
when it itself was evicted.

Verify:
s7d

Change-Id: Id60be398505120db5eb6208875bb94982cd35a3b
Signed-off-by: Jiucheng Xu <jiucheng.xu@amlogic.com>
---
 fs/ntfs3/frecord.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/fs/ntfs3/frecord.c b/fs/ntfs3/frecord.c
index 7a1f57dc58dfc..de59c5ad50931 100644
--- a/fs/ntfs3/frecord.c
+++ b/fs/ntfs3/frecord.c
@@ -3246,6 +3246,9 @@ int ni_write_inode(struct inode *inode, int sync, const char *hint)
 		if (!ntfs_is_meta_file(sbi, inode->i_ino) &&
 		    (modified || (ni->ni_flags & NI_FLAG_UPDATE_PARENT))
 		    /* Avoid __wait_on_freeing_inode(inode). */
+#ifdef CONFIG_AMLOGIC_NTFS3_ISSUE
+		    && !(inode->i_state & (I_FREEING | I_WILL_FREE))
+#endif
 		    && (sb->s_flags & SB_ACTIVE)) {
 			dup.cr_time = std->cr_time;
 			/* Not critical if this function fail. */
-- 
2.46.0

